**Segments**

- **Type:** The global arthritis market can be segmented by type into osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, psoriatic arthritis, ankylosing spondylitis, and others. Osteoarthritis is the most common form of arthritis, affecting millions of people worldwide. It is characterized by the breakdown of cartilage in the joints, leading to pain and stiffness. Rheumatoid arthritis is an autoimmune disease that causes inflammation in the joints, resulting in pain, swelling, and stiffness. Psoriatic arthritis is a type of arthritis that occurs in some people with psoriasis, a skin condition characterized by red, scaly patches. Ankylosing spondylitis primarily affects the spine, causing pain and stiffness in the back and neck.

- **Treatment:** The market can also be segmented by treatment, including medication, physical therapy, surgery, and others. Medications for arthritis include pain relievers, anti-inflammatory drugs, and disease-modifying antirheumatic drugs (DMARDs). Physical therapy can help improve joint function and reduce pain. In severe cases, surgery may be necessary to repair or replace damaged joints.

- **End-User:** On the basis of end-user, the arthritis market can be segmented into hospitals, clinics, ambulatory surgery centers, and others. Hospitals are the primary facilities for the treatment of arthritis, especially for patients requiring surgery or specialized care. Clinics offer outpatient services such as consultations, injections, and physical therapy. Ambulatory surgery centers provide surgical procedures on a same-day basis, offering convenience to patients.

